Installation
-----------

In the root folder, type:

    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    make


Usage
-----

Run r128-sndfile, r128-ffmpeg, r128-mpg123 or r128-musepack with the files you
want to scan as arguments.

The output will look like this:

    $ ./r128-sndfile ~/music/bad\ loop\ -\ Luo/*.flac

    -12.81 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 01 Nio.flac
    -11.15 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 02 Eri Valeire.flac
    -10.14 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 03 Kauniit Ihmiset.flac
    -11.31 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 04 Mmin.flac
    -26.13 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 05 3b Or T.flac
    -14.10 LUFS, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 06 Kannas Nsp.flac
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    -11.75 LUFS

or with more options:

    $ ./r128-sndfile -l -p both ~/music/bad\ loop\ -\ Luo/*.flac

    -12.81 LUFS, LRA: 14.16 LU, sample peak: 0.89151001, true peak: 0.99826229, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 01 Nio.flac
    -11.15 LUFS, LRA: 8.26 LU, sample peak: 0.89163208, true peak: 0.99095666, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 02 Eri Valeire.flac
    -10.14 LUFS, LRA: 11.79 LU, sample peak: 0.89154053, true peak: 0.99171823, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 03 Kauniit Ihmiset.flac
    -11.31 LUFS, LRA: 11.75 LU, sample peak: 0.89157104, true peak: 0.92898595, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 04 Mmin.flac
    -26.13 LUFS, LRA: 14.87 LU, sample peak: 0.25204468, true peak: 0.25203928, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 05 3b Or T.flac
    -14.10 LUFS, LRA: 11.40 LU, sample peak: 0.89151001, true peak: 1.02603507, /home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 06 Kannas Nsp.flac
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    -11.75 LUFS, LRA: 13.34 LU, sample peak: 0.89163208, true peak: 1.02603507

Scripts can parse standard output easily:

    $ ./r128-sndfile -l -p both ~/music/bad\ loop\ -\ Luo/*.flac 2> /dev/null
    -12.81,14.16,0.89151001,0.99826229,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 01 Nio.flac
    -11.15,8.26,0.89163208,0.99095666,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 02 Eri Valeire.flac
    -10.14,11.79,0.89154053,0.99171823,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 03 Kauniit Ihmiset.flac
    -11.31,11.75,0.89157104,0.92898595,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 04 Mmin.flac
    -26.13,14.87,0.25204468,0.25203928,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 05 3b Or T.flac
    -14.10,11.40,0.89151001,1.02603507,/home/jan/music/bad loop - Luo/bad loop - Luo - 06 Kannas Nsp.flac
    -11.75,13.34,0.89163208,1.02603507


The scanners also support ReplayGain tagging with the option "-t". Run it like
this:

    r128-sndfile -t album <directory>

or:

    r128-sndfile -t track <directory>

and it will scan the directory as one album/as tracks. Use the option "-r" to
search recursively for music files and tag them as one album per subfolder. The
tagger also supports file input; then all files are treated as one album.

Use the option "-p" to print information about peak values. Use "-p sample" for
sample peaks, "-p true" for true peaks, and "-p both" to print both values.

The reference volume is -18 LU (5 dB louder than the EBU R 128 reference level
of -23 LU).

All scanners support loudness range measurement with the command line
option "-l".

Use the options "-s", "-m" or "-i" to print short-term (last 3s), momentary
(last 0.4s) or integrated loudness information to stdout. For example:

    r128-sndfile -m 0.1 foo.wav

to print the momentary loudness of foo.wav to stdout every 0.1s.
